    lead: 'Mebaring targets mebaru (rockfish) using worms and plugs — a flagship light-game genre. TSURI HACK\'s beginner article notes that a single jig-tan (jig head + worm) setup is all you need. DAIWA\'s Rintako-style guide details the latest mebaring tackle using the Gekka Bijin series. Tsuri ni Iku\'s guide covers three styles: jig-tan, float rig, and plugging. Mebaru peaks during winter through spring — when other fishing slows down, mebaring thrives. This article covers mebaring fundamentals from tackle selection to practical techniques.',
