    lead: 'Light game is the umbrella term for saltwater lure fishing using lightweight lures to target small-to-medium fish. SHIMANO\'s beginner guide describes ajing and mebaring as specialized subcategories within light game. Tsurugu no Point\'s entry guide notes that one light-game rod can target aji, mebaru, kasago, and seigo. Sunline\'s column recommends beginners start with jig-tan and float rigs before advancing. "Species-unlimited" light game is the ideal gateway to fishing. CAST/LOG\'s database contains over 100 series of aji and mebaru-compatible worms alone.',
