        body: 'Light-game lures fall into three categories: worm + jig head, metal jigs, and plugs. Worm + jig head (jig-tan) is the foundation. Combine 1.5–2.5 inch worms with 0.5–1.5g jig heads. Pin-tail works for aji, shad-tail for mebaru, but both catch either species. Micro metal jigs (3–7g) cover distance and pufferfish situations that worms can\'t handle. Plugs (minnow, sinpen, vibe) are primarily for mebaru but work on aji too. Sunline recommends beginners start with jig-tan, graduating to float rigs and plugs after gaining experience.',
